      "side": 1,
      "message": "I definitely will!  I started our dashboard before discovering the `gerrit-monitoring` project and imported them on the side. They can be seen on our public Grafana at suffixed with `-upstream` https://grafana.wikimedia.org/dashboards/f/5AnaHr2Mk/gerrit\n\nI ended up deleting the one for `replica` because I was not happy with the graphs. The `quantile` labels keep the same value which results in graph for delay and latency to show plateau.  I have use a trick to turn those to zero to when the rate of the associated counter is zero (ie there is no associated replication event at that time), this way we see the gaps.\n\nI also found a way to find the last timestamp a replication happened which let me get some nice panels at the top:\n```\ngithub: an hour ago\nreplica: a few seconds ago\nspare: an hour ago\n```\n(we don\u0027t replicate everything to github, I think the spare is ongoing maintenance).\n\nAnyway I digress, but surely I will upstream my findings when things have settled :-]",
