      "side": 1,
      "message": "To verify I have:\n* downloaded the `replication.jar` generated by Zuul CI\n* loaded `metrics-reporter-prometheus` plugin\n* created a `replication.config` with:\n```\n[gerrit]\n    replicateOnStartup \u003d false\n    autoReload \u003d false\n    defaultForceUpdate \u003d false\n\n[remote \"github\"]\n    url \u003d github@localhost:foobar/${name}\n```\n\nI went to http://127.0.0.1:8080/plugins/metrics-reporter-prometheus/metrics and surely I got the queue metrics showing up:\n```\nqueue_replicate_togithub_active_threads 0.0\nqueue_replicate_togithub_max_pool_size 2.147483647E9\nqueue_replicate_togithub_pool_size 0.0\nqueue_replicate_togithub_scheduled_tasks 0.0\nqueue_replicate_togithub_total_completed_tasks_count 0.0\nqueue_replicate_togithub_total_scheduled_tasks_count 0.0\n```\n\nIt is missing an underscore between `replicate_to` and the replica name `github`. A Gerrit built-in queue would show as: `queue_send_email_active_threads`.\n\nI wonder whether it should be additionally namespaced with the plugin name, for example:\n```\nqueue_plugins_replication_replicate_to_github_active_threads\n```",
      "revId": "f4e9a2ac0011393d335730e88f4d29a1cabc8f38",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
