      "writtenOn": "2026-02-21T21:57:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "WorkQueue uses:\n```\n    private String getMetricName(String queueName, String metricName) {\n      String name \u003d\n          CaseFormat.UPPER_CAMEL.to(\n              CaseFormat.LOWER_UNDERSCORE, queueName.replaceFirst(\"SSH\", \"Ssh\").replace(\"-\", \"\"));\n      return metrics.sanitizeMetricName(String.format(\"queue/%s/%s\", name, metricName));\n    }\n```\nThus given a thread named `ReplicateTo-github-1`:\n- it removes the dash: `ReplicateTogithub\u0027\n- change from camel case to underscore: `replicate_togithub`\n\nThen I can change the remote name to match the code:\n\n- GitHub (camelcase) \u003d\u003e replicate_to_git_hub\n- Github (first upper case) \u003d\u003e replicate_to_github\n\nIt is not ideal, I think the remote name should be preserved but WorkQueue does not allow that. Thus I guess I can document the behavior in the plugin config documentation?",
