      "writtenOn": "2026-02-24T15:41:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I get it right, the queue is created by core which uses `MetricMaker` and because it is not reloadable, there is no point in having the metric unregistered. \n\nPlugins are supposed to use `PluginMetricMaker` which has a stop method:\n```\n@Override\n  public void stop() {\n    synchronized (cleanup) {\n      Iterator\u003cRegistrationHandle\u003e itr \u003d cleanup.iterator();\n      while (itr.hasNext()) {\n        itr.next().remove();\n        itr.remove();\n      }\n    }\n  }\n```\nWhich I guess unregister the metric properly.\n\nSo afterall I should follow Matthias path to introduce a new `WorkQueue.createQueue()` in core which would take a `PluginMetricMaker` to turn on the metric.\n\nThe queues would then be exposed under the plugin prefix?\n\n`plugins_replication_queue_replicate_to_github_pool_size`\n\nWhich is probably cleaner than having a plugin register it without a prefix and messing up with Gerrit core :-]",
